Citation.sAbstract: The solubility of 3-pentadecylphenyl acrylate in n-butanol, toluene, acetone,  dichloromethane, n-heptane and ethyl acetate were measured at the temperatures ranging from  273.15 K to 297.15 K at atmospheric pressure using a laser detecting system. The solubility data were  correlated by the modified Buchowski-Ksiazczak eh equation and Apelblat equation. The calculated  results show that the correlation of the modified Apelblat equation has less deviation than that of the  eh equation. The dissolution enthalpy and entropy of 3-pentadecylphenyl acrylate were predicted with  the solubility data using van't Hoff equation.
Citation.sTitle: Determination of the solubility, dissolution enthalpy and entropy of 3-pentadecylphenyl acrylate  in different organic solvents
